node.text:
Sunsets in Santorini 🌅 Get your photos posted in our account, apply for a feature visiting explorerfervor.com 👉🏼 the link is in our bio: @explorerfervor 

Tag a friend who you’d escape to Greece with!

Loved for its one of a kind architecture and beach views, this Greek town will take your breath away. If you’re visiting Santorini this summer, don’t forget to hike to the town’s volcano and unwind at a winery afterwards ☀️🍷

📷 @cbezerraphotos & @_letstravel_
📍 Santorini, Greece

node.text:
The world’s biggest cat 🦁Share your photos with us and we will post them in our account. Apply for a feature following the link in our bio: @explorerfervor 

It’ s a hybrid offspring of a male lion and a female tiger. It has parents in the same genus but of different species. Distinct from the similar hybrid tigon, and is the largest of all known extant felines. 🐾

📽 @docantle w/ @kodyantle

node.text:
Canada's breathtaking spots via @mthiessen. 🌈 Get your photos posted in our account, apply for a feature visiting explorerfervor.com 👉🏼 the link is in our bio: @explorerfervor 

From natural landscapes to clean and modern cities, Canada is as picturesque as it gets when it comes to spectacular scenery. 🇨🇦

Swipe through and marvel at these incredible places! Save this post for reference when you visit Canada. 📝

@Nature Destinations in Canada
1-3. Niagara Falls, Ontario
4. Spirit Island, Alberta
5. Jasper, Alberta
6. Golden fields near Stony Plain, Alberta
7. Emerald Lake, British Columbia
8. Moraine Lake Road, Alberta
9. Lake Louise, Alberta
10. Edmonton, Alberta

Which one is your favorite? 👇

📸 @mthiessen
📍 Canada

node.text:
Naqshe Jahan Square in #Isfahan has been registered as a World Heritage Site by UNESCO ❤️ We can post your pictures in our account. Check the link in our bio for more info: @explorerfervor 

This historical square embraces some iconic monuments, one of them is Imam Mosque, it’s better to say the one of the most significant ones. This mosque is known also as Shah Mosque.
Imam Mosque is the best example of a thousand-year tradition in building mosques. The mosque is comprised of a main dome, two Shabestans (prayers hall), four porches, four minarets, and also including two seminaries next to the mosque to study theology.

The mosque was built near 400 years ago by the command of Shah Abbas I Safavi, Abbas the Great. The architecture and decorations of the mosque are really picturesque. One of the wonders of its architecture is the angle between the entrance and the main axis of the structure. The Propylaea is toward square to maintain the symmetry and harmony with the other buildings of square, while the structure of mosque is rotated toward Qibla. The wise and talented architect dissolved this rotation by combining some empty space in arch forms, and when you enter the mosque you don’t recognize a rotating plan.

Decorations of the Propylaea are really impressive, especially the magnificent tiles. When you want to enter the mosque, it’s better to take look above to shock. There is a perfect Muqarnas technique which has been decorated by the shrubs. Mihrab is the other significant part of the mosque.

📸 @fatemeghaderi
